‘and now abideth faith, hope, charity, these three; but the greatest of these is charity’ (1 Corinthians 13:13), <i>Charity</i> is less commonly used as a given name than the shorter   Faith   and   Hope ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705207,"age":6,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":8,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705212,"age":41,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705213,"age":63,"year":"1642","toYear":"1651","julianDay":2320789,"title":"The English Civil War","description":"A series of conflicts regarding England's governance during the years 1642 to 1651 is now known as The English Civil War. Charles I summoned supporters to join him against his enemies in Parliament. In October 1642, nearly 10,000 men fought for Charles I and chased Parliament across the River Tamar. Fighting continued for years and was finally ended at the Battle of Worcester on September 3, 1651, with a Parliamentarian victory.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705216,"age":109,"year":"1688","toYear":"1689","julianDay":2337590,"title":"Glorious Revolution","description":"The Glorious Revolution brought the downfall of Catholic King James II and the reign of his Protestant daughter Mary and her Dutch husband, William III of Orange.","url":"http://www.bbc.co.uk/history/british/civil_war_revolution/glorious_revolution_01.shtml","urlTitle":"BBC - Glorious Revolution","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Charity Tabb was born in 1579, in Teignmouth, Devon, England, her father, Mathew Tabb, was 35 and her mother, Charitie Tayller, was 32. She married Thomas Tozier on 14 January 1599, in Teignbridge, Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"1579–":"1579–Surnud","1579–Female":"1579–Surnud","1585–Female":"1585–Surnud","1589–Male":"1589–Surnud","1570–1640":"1570–1640","1620–1675":"1620–1675","1639–Male":"1639–Surnud","1544–Male":"1544–Surnud","1547–Female":"1547–Surnud","14 January 1599":"14. jaanuar 1599","29 January 1580":"29. jaanuar 1580","1570":"1570","1547":"1547","1579":"1579","1689":"1689","1688":"1688","1589":"1589","1544":"1544","1620":"1620","1642":"1642","1587":"1587","1675":"1675","1651":"1651","1640":"1640","1585":"1585","3 November 1639":"3. november 1639","1639":"1639","Stokenham, Stokenham, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Stokenham, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Moretonhampstead, Devon, England":"Moretonhampstead, Devon, England","Teignmouth, Teignbridge, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Teignbridge, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1579–":"1579–Kuollut","1579–Female":"1579–Kuollu